						<summary>

						<p>On the door-jamb, at the entrance (north) into <hi rend="italic">ardhamaṇḍapa,</hi> Ghritasthānēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 10: 981 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that Madhurāntakaṉ Gaṇḍarādittaṉ gave ten buffaloes with which 90 sheep would give the ghee for burning a perpetual lamp for God of Tiruneyttāṉam in Poygai-nāḍu. The shepherds of the village Perumāṉ Vīraṉ and Perumāṉ Gaṇan received the sheep and agreed to measure out one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily (for burning the lamp).</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Āvaṇam</hi> issue No. 19. p. 38.</p>						

						</summary>
